        "description": {
            "value": "<p>To you, crocodilians, giant lizards, and dinosaurs are loyal steeds, not monsters. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Ride]{Ride} feat, even if you don't meet the prerequisites. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Nature checks to Handle an Animal as long as the animal is a reptile, dinosaur, or even a non-sapient dragon.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><em><strong>Note</strong> This feat refers to Nature checks to Handle an Animal. This check does not exist in Pathfinder 2, and so the feat instead gives a bonus to Nature checks to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Command an Animal]{Command an Animal}. </em></p>"
